  "response_text": "# Healthy Eating Plan\n\n## Core Principles\n- **Balance**: Include all food groups daily\n- **Moderation**: Appropriate portion sizes\n- **Variety**: Different foods for diverse nutrients\n- **Hydration**: 8+ glasses of water daily\n\n---\n\n## Daily Food Guidelines\n\n### Vegetables & Fruits (½ your plate)\n- 2-3 cups vegetables (varied colors)\n- 1.5-2 cups fruit\n- *Tip*: Aim for dark leafy greens, orange, and red varieties\n\n### Whole Grains (¼ your plate)\n- 5-8 ounces daily\n- Choose: brown rice, oats, whole wheat bread, quinoa\n- *Tip*: Make half your grains whole grains\n\n### Protein (¼ your plate)\n- 5-6.5 ounces daily\n- Include: lean meats, fish, eggs, beans, nuts, tofu\n- *Tip*: Vary your protein sources\n\n### Dairy\n- 3 cups daily\n- Choose: low-fat or fat-free milk, yogurt, cheese\n- *Alternative*: fortified plant-based options\n\n---\n\n## Sample Daily Menu\n\n**Breakfast**: Oatmeal with berries and almonds\n**Snack**: Greek yogurt with honey\n**Lunch**: Grilled chicken, quinoa, roasted vegetables\n**Snack**: Apple with almond butter\n**Dinner**: Baked salmon, sweet potato, steamed broccoli\n\n---\n\n## Quick Tips\n✓ Meal prep on weekends\n✓ Read nutrition labels\n✓ Limit added sugars and sodium\n✓ Practice portion control\n✓ Eat slowly and mindfully\n\n**Consult a dietitian for personalized advice.**",
